On Sat, Dec 28, 2002 at 10:14:55AM -0800, Courtney Hook wrote:
> Craig, my understanding is that if you have compressed air and your
> valves and rings are in good shape, you can use a sparkplug adapter
> to blow compressed air into the cylinder (like a leakdown tester
> does), when it's on it's compression stroke at TDC, and this will
> keep the valves against their seats. 

another technique is to take some of that 1/4" nylon cord & feed it
into the cylinder at the bottom of it's stroke. then rotate the crank
will the cord will help hold the valves in place.


